snippet.textDisplay: The problem with cable providers is that they have been monopolies; some areas only have one provider, maybe two if they are lucky.  With no competition they were allowed to do what they wanted for decades.  The fact that YouTube TV is like cable is not a BAD thing necessarily.  With YouTube TV, Sling TV and PlayStation Vue people are getting cable at a lower cost than what cable providers charge.  This is making it more of a free market where people have choices and hopefully it will help evolve cable to something better, more affordable, and not full of the B word (bundles) which force you to pay more for stuff you don't want just to watch what you do want.  Cable isn't bad, the companies that run cable is.

snippet.textDisplay:
You haven't watched the finale of BoJack Horseman yet? I miss the days when I could pretty much watch everything I want on Hulu and Netflix.

I still honestly believe Hulu is the best streaming service because if you leave cable which I obviously already did, it's actually the safest option because every episode of a network TV show will come onto Hulu the very next day and you can watch it whenever you want. Eith Netflix you have to wait until like almost a year after an entire season ends to start watching episodes from that show.

and one other thing. It's annoying how Netflix keeps feeling the need to raise their prices especially after losing content while Hulu for the most part keeps increasing content and the price has remained the same. Oftentimes when Netflix loses content you see it pop up on Hulu later like South Park, Futurama, and The Boondocks. Family Guy and American Dad were once on both Hulu and Netflix but now they're just on Hulu. I know I'm just naming off grown up cartoons, they are just the examples I can think of at the moment but there's a lot more examples.
